 "2023-04-29T16:32:19Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "## Problem\n\nVector memory isn't used effectively.\n\n### Related issues (need deduplication):\n* #623\n* #2058\n* #2072\n* #2076\n* #2232\n* #2893\n* #3451\n\n## Areas of improvement\n\n* Restructure memory\n    * Take into account we need to be able to work with related memories, e.g. multiple chunks of a file\n        * Positional encoding?\n    * Effective searching/matching for relevant memories based on current objective/task/step/action (example: SCM4LLMs, although we can probably do better)\n* Rethink how we ingest (large amounts of) data\n    * Recursive chunking?\n\n* *Related: prompt generation*\n    * Contents of a prompt:\n        * Current task\n        * Information/summary w.r.t. the progress of the current task\n        * **Relevant historical/context info from memory**\n        * Result of last action\n        * Instructions on how to judge progress and decide next action (a la AgentGPT)\n    * LMQL could be a significant improvement (tracked in issue #3460, cc @AbTrax)\n\n## \ud83d\udea8 Please no discussion in this thread \ud83d\udea8\n\nThis is a collection issue, intended to collect insights, resources and record progress. If you want to join the discussion on this topic, please do so in the [Discord](https://discord.com/channels/1092243196446249134/1101836856162795581).", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Significant-Gravitas/Auto-GPT/issues/3536/reactions", "total_count": 2, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 2, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Significant-Gravitas/Auto-GPT/issues/3536/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}